http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.value: باد داي (بالإنجليزية: Bud Day)‏ هو ضابط ومحامي أمريكي، ولد في 24 فبراير 1925 في سيوكس سيتي في الولايات المتحدة، وتوفي في 27 يوليو 2013 في فورت والتون بيتش في الولايات المتحدة.

George Everette "Bud" Day (24 February 1925 – 27 July 2013) was a United States Air Force officer, aviator, and veteran of World War II, Korean War and Vietnam War. He was also a prisoner of war, and recipient of the Medal of Honor and Air Force Cross. As of 2016, he is the only person to be awarded both the Medal of Honor and Air Force Cross. He was posthumously advanced to the rank of brigadier general effective March 27, 2018, as directed by the 2017 National Defense Authorization Act.

George Everett "Bud" Day (24 de febrero de 1925 - 27 de julio de 2013) fue un coronel y piloto de la Fuerza Aérea de los Estados Unidos que sirvió durante la Segunda Guerra Mundial, la Guerra de Corea, y la Guerra de Vietnam, incluyendo un periodo como prisionero de guerra de cinco años y siete meses en Vietnam del Norte. Day fue galardonado con la Medalla de Honor y la Cruz de la Fuerza Aérea. Desde 2013, fue la única persona que recibió dos medallas a la vez.

George Everette "Bud" Day merupakan veteran perang Amerika Serikat yang terlibat dalam Perang Dunia Ke-II, Perang Vietnam, Perang Korea serta merupakan veteran dengan medali militer terbanyak setelah Douglas McArthur. Bud dikenal sebagai pilot yang berpengalaman menerbangkan berbagai jenis pesawat militer seperti P-80 Shooting Star, F-84 Thunderjet, F-100 Super Sabre, F-101 Voodoo, F-104 Starfighter, F-105 Thunderchief, F-106 Delta Dart, FB-111, F-4 Phantom II, A-4 Skyhawk, A-7 Corsair II, CF-5 Tiger, F-16, dan F-15 Eagle. Dalam dunia perpolitikan, Bud merupakan anggota dari Partai Republikan dan berkampanye bersama John McCain pada tahun 2000 dan 2008.

http://dbpedia.org/ontology/abstract.value: George Everette "Bud" Day (24 February 1925 – 27 July 2013) was a United States Air Force officer, aviator, and veteran of World War II, Korean War and Vietnam War. He was also a prisoner of war, and recipient of the Medal of Honor and Air Force Cross. As of 2016, he is the only person to be awarded both the Medal of Honor and Air Force Cross. He was posthumously advanced to the rank of brigadier general effective March 27, 2018, as directed by the 2017 National Defense Authorization Act. Day's actions from 26 August 1967 through 14 March 1973 were the last to earn the Medal of Honor prior to the end of U.S. involvement in the Vietnam War on 30 April 1975, though some honorees (e.g. Leslie H. Sabo Jr., honored on 16 May 2012) were cited for their medals after Day's recognition on 4 March 1976. Having earned over 70 , Day is considered to be the most decorated United States military officer since Douglas MacArthur.
